      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Blockages in the pitot tube can come from a variety of sources, including insects, ice, snow, and even debris from bird strikes. On a Cessna 172, it's relatively common for birds to impact the pitot tube, especially during winter months. In extreme cases, a blockage can cause the airspeed indicator to show wildly inaccurate readings, potentially leading to loss of situational awareness or even control issues during an emergency.",
